          You ain't got nothin'.


231
00:15:42,976 --> 00:15:45,310
Twenty bucks for a hint?        


232
00:15:45,345 --> 00:15:50,048
           And another $20      
           for your wallet back.


233
00:15:50,083 --> 00:15:51,582
<i>(Josh)</i>                          
<i>Unbelievable.</i>                   


234
00:15:55,922 --> 00:15:57,422
Where are your parents?         


235
00:15:57,457 --> 00:15:58,923
                            L.A.


236
00:15:58,959 --> 00:16:01,092
                <i> I'm just here</i>  
                <i> for the summer.</i>


237
00:16:01,127 --> 00:16:03,261
     They thought I was hangin' 
     around with the wrong sort,


238
00:16:03,296 --> 00:16:06,831
             so it was either   
             here or Bible camp,


239
00:16:06,866 --> 00:16:08,333
                 more or less   
                 the same thing.


240
00:16:08,368 --> 00:16:10,601
Yeah, we're such                
a burden, I know.               


241
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:12,103
                Uh-oh, too late.


242
00:16:12,138 --> 00:16:13,938
Give the man back               
his property, young lady.       


243
00:16:13,974 --> 00:16:16,807
<i>Stealin's not right.</i>            
<i>You know that.</i>                  


244
00:16:16,843 --> 00:16:20,044
                Selling guns is?


245
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,946
See what I put up with?         


246
00:16:21,982 --> 00:16:23,448
           Adorable.            


247
00:16:23,483 --> 00:16:25,316
<i>(Grandpa)</i>                       
<i>Hey, you have</i>                   
<i>an answer for me?</i>               


248
00:16:26,386 --> 00:16:28,186
      Don't move, old man!      
      I'll roast you!           


249
00:16:28,221 --> 00:16:30,054
       Hands up! Come on!       


250
00:16:30,090 --> 00:16:32,756
       <i> Come on, come on,</i>       
       <i> come on.</i>                


251
00:16:32,792 --> 00:16:35,759
 <i> You fill this bag up</i>          
 <i> with automatics and cash now!</i> 


252
00:16:35,795 --> 00:16:37,261
Okay, anything you want.        
Anything you want.              


253
00:16:37,297 --> 00:16:38,762
<i>Just don't hurt her!</i>            


254
00:16:38,798 --> 00:16:40,365
     I'm givin' the orders,     
     old man. Do it!            


255
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:42,566
         - Okay, okay.          
         - Come on!             


256
00:16:42,602 --> 00:16:44,068
            <i> Uh-huh.</i>            


257
00:16:44,104 --> 00:16:46,237
       - Hey, I know you.       
       - Jeff!                  


258
00:16:46,272 --> 00:16:49,407
   This here's a pretty one.    
   Can I have her?              


259
00:16:49,442 --> 00:16:51,609
   - Keep your hands off her!   
   - Shut up your face!         


260
00:16:51,644 --> 00:16:53,111
         <i> Move! Come on!</i>        


261
00:16:53,146 --> 00:16:54,778
        Alright, quick,         
        quick, quick.           


262
00:16:54,814 --> 00:16:56,314
             <i> Hurry!</i>            


263
00:16:57,617 --> 00:16:59,750
      We're in, boss.           
      Three minutes, tops.      


264
00:17:00,253 --> 00:17:01,752
           How many?            


265
00:17:02,722 --> 00:17:04,188
          - There.              
          - That's it?          


266
00:17:04,224 --> 00:17:05,990
<i>(Grandpa)</i>                       
<i>Yeah.</i>                           


267
00:17:06,026 --> 00:17:07,492
       Anybody else here?       


268
00:17:07,527 --> 00:17:09,494
   - No, go on.                 
   - Is there anyone else? -    


269
00:17:09,529 --> 00:17:11,095
No, no! Okay,                   
you got what you wanted.        


270
00:17:11,131 --> 00:17:16,134
  <i> (thug)</i>                       
  <i> It's just the three of them,</i> 
  <i> the owner and two others.</i>    


271
00:17:23,076 --> 00:17:25,410
         No witnesses.          


272
00:17:26,179 --> 00:17:30,714
           [thunder]            


273
00:17:31,418 --> 00:17:32,917
           [laughing]           


274
00:17:36,356 --> 00:17:39,590
<i>(thug)</i>                          
<i>Sorry, partner.</i>                 
<i>You heard the boss.</i>             


275
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:44,095
Adios, amigo.                   


276
00:17:57,110 --> 00:18:08,352
                             ♪♪♪


277
00:18:14,260 --> 00:18:15,726
        [rapid gunshots]        


278
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:17,261
         [girl screams]         


279
00:18:17,730 --> 00:18:19,230
           [gunshot]            


280
00:18:22,969 --> 00:18:24,668
                 <i> (thug)</i>        
                 <i> You gonna die!</i>


281
00:18:27,140 --> 00:18:28,639
           [gunshot]            


282
00:18:37,150 --> 00:18:41,152
                             ♪♪♪


283
00:18:41,187 --> 00:18:44,855
               <i> (thug)</i>          
               <i> You are so</i>      
               <i> completely dead!</i>


284
00:18:44,890 --> 00:18:46,390
                        [laughs]


285
00:18:46,426 --> 00:18:47,925
          <i> [cocks and fires gun]</i>


286
00:18:51,231 --> 00:18:53,531
       Something's wrong.       


287
00:18:53,566 --> 00:18:55,566
     <i> You three, you're in.</i>     


288
00:18:56,336 --> 00:18:57,835
              No.               


289
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:02,106
     You're too important.      


290
00:19:03,109 --> 00:19:04,609
         I'm going too.         


291
00:19:08,981 --> 00:19:11,516
         Everybody else         
         back to camp.          


292
00:19:11,551 --> 00:19:14,852
    You go where I tell you.    


293
00:19:16,956 --> 00:19:18,589
          <i> [cocks and fires gun]</i>


294
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:27,731
                             ♪♪♪


295
00:19:27,767 --> 00:19:29,267
                       [gunshot]


296
00:19:30,336 --> 00:19:32,370
        [rapid gunshots]        


297
00:19:35,074 --> 00:19:39,877
     [grunting and moaning]     


298
00:19:46,886 --> 00:19:55,993
                             ♪♪♪


299
00:19:56,028 --> 00:20:03,033
      [automatic gunfire]       


300
00:20:04,704 --> 00:20:06,204
Where are the others?           


301
00:20:08,208 --> 00:20:09,674
       They're all dead.        


302
00:20:09,709 --> 00:20:12,109
  - We can't leave 'em behind.  
  - Forget it! We go!           


303
00:20:12,978 --> 00:20:14,478
   <i> (thug)</i>                      
   <i> Let's get him outta here.</i>   


304
00:20:22,088 --> 00:20:33,364
                             ♪♪♪


305
00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:34,898
You alright, honey?             


306
00:20:36,536 --> 00:20:38,102
Stay.                           


307
00:20:39,939 --> 00:20:47,978
                             ♪♪♪


308
00:20:48,013 --> 00:20:50,814
How did you?                    


309
00:20:50,850 --> 00:20:52,950
Who are you?                    


310
00:20:54,587 --> 00:20:57,488
        [lightning clap]        


311
00:21:03,829 --> 00:21:05,796
         <i> (thug leader)</i>         
         <i> Who did this?</i>         


312
00:21:05,831 --> 00:21:08,766
    <i> Who killed our brothers?</i>   
    <i> Was it the old man?</i>        


313
00:21:08,801 --> 00:21:12,336
<i>(thug)</i>                          
<i>No, it was</i>                      
<i>the other guy.</i>                  


314
00:21:12,372 --> 00:21:17,007
<i>We didn't</i>                       
<i>pay him no mind,</i>                


315
00:21:17,042 --> 00:21:19,277
<i>and I tried.</i>                    


316
00:21:19,912 --> 00:21:22,112
        - You did good.         
        - But I tried.          


317
00:21:22,148 --> 00:21:24,248
       You did real good.       


318
00:21:28,053 --> 00:21:30,421
    I'm gonna send you home.    


319
00:21:32,492 --> 00:21:37,795
     [muffled suffocating]      


320
00:21:39,732 --> 00:21:49,774
                             ♪♪♪


321
00:21:49,776 --> 00:21:54,745
                             ♪♪♪


322
00:22:01,153 --> 00:22:04,188
     <i> (thug leader)</i>             
     <i> They're all gonna pay.</i>    


323
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:14,832
                             ♪♪♪


324
00:22:14,867 --> 00:22:18,502
    [muffled voice speaking]    


325
00:22:19,639 --> 00:22:22,272
   <i> (police officer)</i>            
   <i> So let me get this straight.</i>


326
00:22:22,308 --> 00:22:26,610
  You took down these           
  three guys, all of them armed,


327
00:22:26,646 --> 00:22:29,513
           in, what was that,   
           less than 20 seconds?


328
00:22:29,549 --> 00:22:32,282
Um...I guess.                   


329
00:22:32,318 --> 00:22:33,784
         I told ya.             
         He was like...         


330
00:22:33,820 --> 00:22:37,321
    [making fighting noises]    


331
00:22:37,690 --> 00:22:39,923
    Lieutenant,                 
    you gotta see this tape.    


332
00:22:39,959 --> 00:22:44,762
<i>(Grandpa)</i>                       
<i>Yeah, where'd</i>                   
<i>you train, son?</i>                 


333
00:22:44,797 --> 00:22:47,732
I've never seen                 
anything like this.             


334
00:22:48,835 --> 00:22:50,300
      Look, those guys          
      were gonna kill us.       


335
00:22:50,336 --> 00:22:52,102
     I had to do something.     


336
00:22:52,137 --> 00:22:54,739
  <i> I just--I got lucky, really.</i> 


337
00:22:54,774 --> 00:22:56,340
                   <i> (Lieutenant)</i>
                   <i> Lucky?</i>      


338
00:22:56,376 --> 00:22:58,542
      I mean, do you expect     
      any of us to believe that?


339
00:22:58,578 --> 00:23:02,880
<i>(Grandpa)</i>                       
<i>Well, however you did it, it's</i>  
<i>a miracle we're still alive.</i>    


340
00:23:02,915 --> 00:23:05,850
Bless you, son.                 
Bless you.                      


341
00:23:05,885 --> 00:23:07,852
  <i> (Lieutenant)</i>                 
  <i> Alright, look, let's</i>         
  <i> head on down to the station.</i> 


342
00:23:07,887 --> 00:23:09,653
   We got a lot                 
   of paperwork to fill out.    


343
00:23:09,689 --> 00:23:11,655
     - Ooh, can I come too?     
     - No, young lady.          


344
00:23:11,691 --> 00:23:13,591
You need to rest.               
I'm takin' you home.            


345
00:23:13,626 --> 00:23:15,092
          Oh, come on.          


346
00:23:15,127 --> 00:23:18,729
And Josh, I expect to see you   
at noon for lunch at my place,  


347
00:23:18,765 --> 00:23:20,964
so I can                        
thank you properly.             


348
00:23:22,134 --> 00:23:25,903
           [rumbling]           


349
00:23:29,942 --> 00:23:31,809
       <i> (officer)</i>               
       <i> What is goin' on?</i>       


350
00:23:31,844 --> 00:23:33,544
       The whole world's        
       fallin' apart.           


351
00:23:33,579 --> 00:23:36,146
Yeah, I don't know.             


352
00:23:36,181 --> 00:23:37,648
         Thanks, Frank.         


353
00:23:37,683 --> 00:23:40,451
 I appreciate that, but         
 I gotta get home to my family. 


354
00:23:40,486 --> 00:23:41,952
    <i> (Lieutenant)</i>               
    <i> That's not gonna happen.</i>   


355
00:23:41,987 --> 00:23:44,154
 Look, you need to stay         
 around town for a couple days  


356
00:23:44,189 --> 00:23:45,823
      <i> until we straighten</i>      
      <i> this mess out.</i>           


357
00:23:45,858 --> 00:23:47,525
Then it's settled.              


358
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:50,761
<i>Noon we eat</i>                     
<i>and give thanks.</i>                


359
00:23:53,433 --> 00:24:03,474
                             ♪♪♪


360
00:24:03,476 --> 00:24:08,412
                             ♪♪♪


361
00:24:08,448 --> 00:24:18,489
                             ♪♪♪


362
00:24:18,491 --> 00:24:23,427
                             ♪♪♪


363
00:24:23,463 --> 00:24:35,940
                             ♪♪♪


364
00:24:35,975 --> 00:24:38,041
        Was it worth it?        


365
00:24:40,279 --> 00:24:41,779
       Take him out back.       


366
00:24:41,814 --> 00:24:43,881
           Burn him.            


367
00:24:45,685 --> 00:24:47,751
   Make sure you do it right.   


368
00:24:49,355 --> 00:24:51,522
        Ditch the truck.        


369
00:24:52,424 --> 00:24:56,660
<i>(thug)</i>                          
<i>Boss, what are</i>                  
<i>we gonna do now?</i>                


370
00:25:02,468 --> 00:25:08,839
        We find him,            
        this other guy,         


371
00:25:08,875 --> 00:25:12,142
      and the owner             
      and his family too.       


372
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:15,579
Let me go.                      


373
00:25:15,615 --> 00:25:17,080
              Why?              


374
00:25:17,116 --> 00:25:18,949
       So you can               
       fix your mistake?        


375
00:25:18,985 --> 00:25:21,284
I can do this.                  


376
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:23,687
      - Go with her.            
      - You got it, boss.       


377
00:25:23,723 --> 00:25:27,691
I don't need him.               


378
00:25:27,727 --> 00:25:29,326
            Get the information,
            and get home.       


379
00:25:29,361 --> 00:25:30,828
           <i> (thug)</i>              
           <i> I'm on it.</i>          


380
00:25:30,863 --> 00:25:33,631
I said I don't need him!        


381
00:25:33,666 --> 00:25:35,666
                 Did I stutter?!


382
00:25:35,701 --> 00:25:37,367
         I want this done right.


383
00:25:37,403 --> 00:25:39,102
               No more mistakes.


384
00:25:39,138 --> 00:25:40,638
        Let me go, then.        


385
00:25:41,040 --> 00:25:44,307
       Everybody                
       get away from me!        


386
00:25:55,588 --> 00:25:57,821
        Are you worthy?         


387
00:26:04,363 --> 00:26:07,731
<i>(Sheriff)</i>                       
<i>Sorry about all this,</i>           
<i>but I'm gonna need</i>              


388
00:26:07,767 --> 00:26:12,770
to keep you in town the next    
4 or 5 days, give or take.      


389
00:26:12,805 --> 00:26:14,304
Just procedure.                 


390
00:26:15,374 --> 00:26:19,476
               Ah, my wife's not
               gonna like that, 


391
00:26:19,511 --> 00:26:22,145
                     not at all.


392
00:26:22,181 --> 00:26:23,814
Consider it a vacation.         


393
00:26:23,849 --> 00:26:25,449
I mean, look around you.        


394
00:26:25,484 --> 00:26:27,017
You couldn't wish               
for a finer destination.        


395
00:26:27,053 --> 00:26:30,554
You can visit our               
strip mine or scrap yard.       


396
00:26:30,590 --> 00:26:32,556
      <i> (Lieutenant)</i>             
      <i> I think Eddie Bunce</i>      
      <i> has got a new cow.</i>       


397
00:26:32,592 --> 00:26:36,560
<i>(Sheriff)</i>                       
<i>There you go.</i>                   
<i>The independent zoo.</i>            


398
00:26:36,596 --> 00:26:39,029
           Uh, I'll just go     
           to the nearest motel.


399
00:26:39,065 --> 00:26:40,965
      <i> (Lieutenant)</i>             
      <i> That'd be the</i>            
      <i> Pear Blossom Motel.</i>      


400
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:43,934
     Straight shot              
     about 10 miles south.      


401
00:26:43,970 --> 00:26:45,970
                         Thanks.


402
00:26:52,812 --> 00:26:57,247
       Are you sure you're okay?


403
00:26:57,282 --> 00:27:00,317
I'm fine. Why?                  


404
00:27:00,352 --> 00:27:05,355
             Well, you know,    
             one of our deputies


405
00:27:05,390 --> 00:27:07,557
               had to kill a man
               a while back.    


406
00:27:07,593 --> 00:27:10,094
        He ain't been           
        right in the head since.


407
00:27:10,129 --> 00:27:14,297
       Messed him up pretty bad.


408
00:27:14,333 --> 00:27:16,533
              It's quite a thing
              to take a life.   


409
00:27:16,568 --> 00:27:18,535
         You know, I still get  
         the jitters about a man


410
00:27:18,570 --> 00:27:25,075
 I pulled a gun on,             
 and that was some 20 years ago.


411
00:27:25,111 --> 00:27:29,113
Well, I've had experience.      


412
00:27:29,148 --> 00:27:31,481
                 Is that a fact?


413
00:27:31,517 --> 00:27:35,452
             You been in combat?


414
00:27:35,487 --> 00:27:36,954
Can't really                    
talk about it.                  


415
00:27:36,989 --> 00:27:38,856
          Yeah, I bet.          


416
00:27:38,891 --> 00:27:41,391
       <i> Seen your records.</i>      


417
00:27:41,426 --> 00:27:44,995
    They're completely blank    
    before 5 years ago.         


418
00:27:45,031 --> 00:27:46,496
     You didn't even exist.     


419
00:27:46,532 --> 00:27:48,866
                  Is that right?


420
00:27:48,901 --> 00:27:52,836
         Some kind of CIA G-Man?


421
00:27:52,872 --> 00:27:55,005
       <i> Yeah, yeah,</i>             
       <i> you can't talk about it.</i>


422
00:27:55,041 --> 00:27:56,940
             Well, I'm just glad
             you're on our side.


423
00:27:56,976 --> 00:27:58,842
                  Tell you what.


424
00:27:58,878 --> 00:28:07,151
                             ♪♪♪


425
00:28:07,186 --> 00:28:08,886
            <i> (thug)</i>             
            <i> Come on.</i>           


426
00:28:10,022 --> 00:28:13,891
           You did a darn good  
           thing today, McManus.


427
00:28:13,926 --> 00:28:16,193
         Saved some good people.


428
00:28:16,228 --> 00:28:17,728
Thank you.                      


429
00:28:24,503 --> 00:28:27,805
So, uh, you gonna               
catch these guys?               


430
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:31,274
 Well, those barbarians         
 are a rough crew from up north.


431
00:28:31,310 --> 00:28:32,776
            We got the call out.


432
00:28:32,812 --> 00:28:34,277
               <i> Don't you worry.</i>
               <i> We'll catch 'em.</i>


433
00:28:34,313 --> 00:28:35,779
    <i> (Lieutenant)</i>               
    <i> You hurt 'em bad today.</i>    


434
00:28:35,815 --> 00:28:38,082
I bet they're runnin' home with 
their tails between their legs. 


435
00:28:38,117 --> 00:28:40,517
                      Bet on it.


436
00:28:48,393 --> 00:28:50,094
            [sighs]             


437
00:28:52,732 --> 00:29:07,144
                             ♪♪♪


438
00:29:07,179 --> 00:29:09,747
   <i> (thug voiceovers)</i>           
   <i> - How much money you got?</i>   
   <i> - Can I have her?</i>           


439
00:29:09,782 --> 00:29:12,649
        <i> - Adios, amigo.</i>        
        <i> - No witnesses.</i>        


440
00:29:19,024 --> 00:29:20,523
          [screaming]           


441
00:29:25,364 --> 00:29:26,864
           [gunshot]            


442
00:29:29,268 --> 00:29:34,271
      [cell phone ringing]      


443
00:29:42,181 --> 00:29:44,748
      [ringing continues]       


444
00:29:45,584 --> 00:29:47,217
           Hey honey.           


445
00:29:47,253 --> 00:29:49,219
       I'm sorry I didn't       
       call you back.           


446
00:29:49,255 --> 00:29:50,720
         I got mixed up         
         in this mess,          


447
00:29:50,756 --> 00:29:55,458
    and I gotta stick around    
    for a few days.             


448
00:29:55,494 --> 00:29:58,495
  I'm sorry I haven't been      
  there for you lately, honey.  


449
00:29:58,530 --> 00:30:02,966
            I just--            


450
00:30:03,002 --> 00:30:07,070
    I've been goin' through     
    a rough time lately.        


451
00:30:07,106 --> 00:30:12,342
  There's some things about me  
  that I haven't told you,      


452
00:30:12,377 --> 00:30:19,249
     things that I thought      
     I could contain.           


453
00:30:19,285 --> 00:30:21,185
        <i> (Frank on phone)</i>       
        <i> Josh?</i>                  


454
00:30:21,220 --> 00:30:23,753
           Mr. Ellis?           


455
00:30:26,992 --> 00:30:28,525
           I'm sorry.           


456
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:31,661
   I thought that you were--    


457
00:30:31,697 --> 00:30:36,934
       it's been a rough        
       day, week, month.        


