00:54:40,978 --> 00:54:43,845
              I'm beginning to  
              think that's true.


785
00:54:49,520 --> 00:54:52,020
              <i> Sorry. I'm sorry.</i>


786
00:54:52,055 --> 00:54:54,122
       <i> (Dylan)</i>                 
       <i> Mommy, I'm hungry.</i>      


787
00:54:54,158 --> 00:54:55,624
We're leavin', baby.            


788
00:54:55,660 --> 00:54:57,660
        I wanna go home.        


789
00:54:57,695 --> 00:54:59,595
Me too.                         


790
00:55:15,680 --> 00:55:17,813
          <i> (Josh)</i>               
          <i> Ah, come on.</i>         


791
00:55:21,786 --> 00:55:26,154
Seems like we're always         
searching for more.             


792
00:55:26,190 --> 00:55:28,990
Go ahead.                       


793
00:55:29,026 --> 00:55:31,159
                       You sure?


794
00:55:31,195 --> 00:55:32,828
It's what good                  
neighbors do, right?            


795
00:55:32,863 --> 00:55:34,963
They take care                  
of each other?                  


796
00:55:37,501 --> 00:55:39,000
                         Thanks.


797
00:55:45,142 --> 00:55:48,744
       You look like you're     
       having one of those days.


798
00:55:48,779 --> 00:55:51,079
You have no idea.               


799
00:55:55,720 --> 00:55:59,020
             Yeah, times        
             are tough all over.


800
00:55:59,056 --> 00:56:04,259
<i>It feels like the whole world's</i> 
<i>fallin' apart, if you ask me.</i>   


801
00:56:04,294 --> 00:56:07,596
                  Where'd all   
                  the heroes go?


802
00:56:07,631 --> 00:56:09,965
                  What happened 
                  to the Titans?


803
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:13,669
     <i> I mean, they had the power</i>
     <i> to change the world.</i>      


804
00:56:13,704 --> 00:56:15,170
         <i> When I look around now</i>


805
00:56:15,205 --> 00:56:20,542
         all I see are children 
         cryin' for their mamas.


806
00:56:23,814 --> 00:56:28,016
No, they're still out there     
on the front lines.             


807
00:56:28,051 --> 00:56:29,518
I've known                      
some good men.                  


808
00:56:29,553 --> 00:56:32,588
Fought alongside of 'em.        


809
00:56:32,623 --> 00:56:34,790
            So you're a warrior?


810
00:56:37,895 --> 00:56:40,028
       You don't look like much.


811
00:56:41,265 --> 00:56:43,331
       <i> Makes me sick when I see</i>
       <i> warriors takin' orders</i>  


812
00:56:43,367 --> 00:56:46,869
               from little men  
               with little ties.


813
00:56:48,806 --> 00:56:53,709
       <i> You know, someday soon</i>  
       <i> there'll be a reckoning.</i>


814
00:56:53,744 --> 00:56:55,210
            It's when the Titans
            will stand up.      


815
00:56:55,245 --> 00:56:56,912
    They'll take back this world
    from the lawyers            


816
00:56:56,947 --> 00:56:58,447
            and the politicians.


817
00:57:00,384 --> 00:57:02,384
               What do you      
               think about that?


818
00:57:20,771 --> 00:57:25,407
I think what you call a Titan,  
I call a tyrant;                


819
00:57:25,443 --> 00:57:31,413
<i>men without compassion,</i>         
<i>men who murder and steal,</i>       


820
00:57:31,449 --> 00:57:33,549
call it their right.            


821
00:57:36,153 --> 00:57:37,920
God willing, there will         
always be men like me           


822
00:57:37,955 --> 00:57:41,122
to put the tyrants              
in their place.                 


823
00:57:46,697 --> 00:57:49,397
Thanks for the change.          


824
00:57:53,370 --> 00:57:56,137
                Glad I could    
                take care of ya.


825
00:57:56,173 --> 00:57:58,106
         [door closing]         


826
00:57:58,809 --> 00:58:03,612
        Finally,                
        somebody worth fighting.


827
00:58:30,007 --> 00:58:32,708
       [laughing quietly]       


828
00:58:34,311 --> 00:58:38,380
       Ugh, do I need           
       to leave the room?       


829
00:58:40,450 --> 00:58:42,150
        <i> [glass breaking]</i>       


830
00:58:43,988 --> 00:58:47,022
      - Frank, what is it?      
      - Shh, quiet.             


